  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I import my Gmail contacts into Skype?",
  "response": "As of my last knowledge update in October 2023, Skype does not have a direct feature to import Gmail contacts. However, you can manually add your Gmail contacts to your Skype account by following these steps:\n\n1. **Export Contacts from Gmail:**\n   - Go to [Google Contacts](https://contacts.google.com).\n   - Sign in with your Gmail account if prompted.\n   - Click on the **\"Export\"** option (typically found in the left-hand menu).\n   - Choose the contacts you want to export or select \"All Contacts.\"\n   - Select the format for the export. For importing into applications like Skype, it\u2019s often best to choose the **\"Google CSV\"** format.\n   - Click on the **\"Export\"** button to download the CSV file to your computer.\n\n2. **Import Contacts into Skype:**\n   - Open Skype and sign in to your account.\n   - Go to the **Contacts** tab or section.\n   - Look for an option to **Add Contacts** or **Import Contacts**.\n   - If there's an import option, you will need to choose the file you've just exported from your Gmail (the CSV file).\n   - Follow any on-screen instructions to complete the contact import. NOTE: Up until my last update, Skype does not support direct CSV import, so you may need to add contacts manually by searching for them by email.\n\n3. **Manual Addition (if necessary):**\n   - If you cannot import the contacts directly, you can manually add them in Skype.\n   - In the Skype application, use the **Search** bar to enter the email addresses or names of your Gmail contacts.\n   - When you find them, you can click on their profile and select **Add Contact**.\n\nPlease keep in mind that Skype's features may have changed after my last update, so it's a good idea to check Skype's help center or support for the most current instructions or any new features.",
